{
  "name": "hydra.print.emacs.regex",
  "metadata": {
    "description": "Per-dialect printer rendering the hydra.regex AST into GNU Emacs regexp syntax. Emacs inverts several escaping conventions relative to POSIX ERE (probe-verified, Emacs 28.2): alternation is \\| (bare | is literal), grouping is \\( \\) (bare ( ) are literal), and bounded quantifiers are \\{n,m\\} (bare braces are literal). The quantifiers * + ? are bare as usual, and character classes are POSIX-like. Hydra's . (any incl. newline) renders as [^z-a] — an empty negated range that matches every character including newline (Emacs . excludes newline). See docs/specification/regex.md and issue #567.",
    "comments": [],
    "seeAlso": []},
  "dependencies": [
    {"module": "hydra.paths"},
    {"module": "hydra.ast"},
    {"module": "hydra.coders"},
